sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT provider_id) AS attending_physicians_count
FROM provider_facility
WHERE role = 'attending physician';

external_knowledge:
Primary specialty refers to the main area of medical expertise for a healthcare provider; 
A facility is a healthcare establishment where providers practice; 
Patient count refers to the number of unique patients a provider has seen; 
Appointment count is the total number of appointments a provider has had; 
Total billing amount is the sum of charges for services provided by a healthcare provider; 
Primary insurance coverage percentage is the proportion of a provider's patients who have primary insurance coverage.
